This\nsuggests a possible origin of the extended [CII] structure from the cooling of\nhot ionized outflows. The extended [CII] and high-velocity [OIII] emission may\nboth contribute in part to the high $L_{\\rm [OIII]}$/$L_{\\rm [CII]}$ ratios\nrecently reported in $z>6$ galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Jun 2022 16:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-03"}
