\ndetected an RV signal near 18 days (FAP < 4.6%), which is half of the stellar\nrotation period. Two Keplerians alone fail at modelling GJ 832b and a second\nplanet with a 35-day orbital period. Moreover, the Bayesian evidence from the\nGP analysis of the RV data with simultaneous activity indices prefers a model\nwithout a second Keplerian, therefore negating the existence of planet c.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Jun 2022 14:12:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 16 Jun 2022 13:26:34 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 4 Jul 2022 12:06:23 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Tue, 2 Aug 2022 15:06:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-16"}
